description:
Daryl's Restoration Over-Hall

EPISODE 8: Everything and the Kitchen Sink

The addition to Daryl's 1787 farmhouse is getting very close to wrapping up, but there's still plenty of work that needs to be done. Now it's time for Daryl to tackle the kitchen and he gives every detail his attention. Custom made, period accurate cabinets help give the room a historic look. Daryl sets off for Massachusetts, hoping to hunt down a vintage, refinished iron stove, an antique apothecary table and salvaged boards for the floor to round out the room. However, finding the right stain for the wood paneled walls becomes a challenge.
